Commentary Text: Maxwell to du Plessis, out Caught by Navdeep Saini!! .. and Maxwell has struck straightaway. RCB have both openers now - tossed up and sliding down leg, du Plessis went a long way across on the sweep, was perhaps undone by a little bit of bounce, gets a top-edge that travelled at pace to short fine - Saini moved across quickly, slid across and then held on in front of his face. Commentary Text: Chahal to Ruturaj Gaikwad, out Caught by Kohli!! That's a stunning catch, Kohli is claiming it as he's chuffed to bits - but Gaikwad isn't going anywhere. In fact, he's asked by his partner to stay on. It's a fair delivery and think Kohli has scooped it just above the turf - one look and the third umpire, Michael Gough, is happy. OUT is the call. That's a much needed wicket for RCB, they needed something now - the game was fast slipping away from their grasp. Top top effort from Kohli, raced forward from backward point, knew that the ball was dying onto him, dived forward and then got both hands under to scoop it. Was the leg-break and Gaikwad didn't spot it - was looking to drive and got a thick edge. Would have got away with it on another day and against any other fielder, but not the Indian captain. Ruturaj Gaikwad c Kohli b Chahal 38(26) [4s-4 6s-1]
